0edlia]], Brazil\n|}\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Peru}}\n*[[Largest cities in the Americas]]\n*[[List of districts of Lima]]\n*[[List of metropolitan areas of Peru]]\n*[[List of people from Lima]]\n*[[List of sites of interest in the Lima Metropolitan area]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n===Further reading===\n{{refbegin|30em}}\n\n====General====\n*''Nota etimol\u00f3gica: El top\u00f3nimo Lima'', Rodolfo Cerr\u00f3n-Palomino, Pontificia Universidad Cat\u00f3lica del Per\u00fa\n*''Lima Monumento Hist\u00f3rico'', Margarita Cubillas Soriano, Lima, 1996\n\n====History====\n*{{cite book|first=Kenneth J. |last=Andrien|title=Crisis and Decline: The Viceroyalty of Peru in the Seventeenth Century|url={{google books |plainurl=y |id=ahS3AAAAIAAJ}}|year=1985|publisher=University of New Mexico Press|isbn=978-0-8263-0791-0|ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book|first=Timothy E. |last=Anna|title=The Fall of the Royal Government in Peru|url={{google books |plainurl=y |id=T4oaAAAAYAAJ}}|year=1979|publisher=University of Nebraska Press|isbn=978-0-8032-1004-2|ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book|last1=Conlee |first1=Christina|first2=Jalh |last2=Dulanto|first3=Carol |last3=Mackay |first4= Charles |last4=Stanish |chapter=Late Prehispanic sociopolitical complexity |editor-first1=Helaine |editor-last1= Silverman |title=Andean archaeology |location=Malden |publisher=Blackwell|year=2004 |pp=209\u2013236 |isbn=0-631-23400-4 |ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book|first=Henry A. |last=Dietz|title=Poverty and Problem-Solving Under Military Rule: The Urban Poor in Lima, Peru|url={{google books |plainurl=y |id=-EnBAAAAIAAJ}}|date=1 January 1980|publisher=University of Texas Press|isbn=978-0-292-76460-6|ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book|first=John |last=Hemming|title=The Conquest of the Incas|url={{google books |plainurl=y |id=QnIaAAAAYAAJ}}|date=1 January 1970|publisher=Harcourt, Brace, Jovanovich|isbn=978-0-15-122560-6|ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book|first=James |last=Higgins|title=Lima: A Cultural History|url={{google books |plainurl=y |id=h0NZ7dAiJ7sC}}|date=January 2005|publisher=Oxford University Press|isbn=978-0-19-517891-3|ref=harv}}\n*Higgins, James (editor). ''The Emancipation of Peru: British Eyewitness Accounts'', 2014. Online at https://sites.google.com/site/jhemanperu\n*{{in lang|es}} Instituto Nacional de Estad\u00edstica e Inform\u00e1tica. ''Lima Metropolitana perfil socio-demogr\u00e1fico''. Lima: INEI, 1996.\n*{{cite book|first=Peter F. |last=Klar\u00e9n|title=Peru: Society and Nationhood in the Andes|url={{google books |plainurl=y |id=6t0R_UUnX1EC}}|year=2000|publisher=Oxford University Press|isbn=978-0-19-506928-0|ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book|last=Ram\u00f3n |first=Gabriel |chapter=The script of urban surgery: Lima, 1850\u20131940 |pp=170\u2013192|editor-first=Arturo Almandoz |editor-last=Marte|title=Planning Latin America's Capital Cities, 1850-1950|url={{google books |plainurl=y |id=eJ0mTbevsA4C}}|year=2002|publisher=Psychology Press|isbn=978-0-415-27265-0|ref=harv}}\n*{{cite web|url=http://hahr.dukejournals.org/content/83/1/53|title=The Upper Classes and Their Upper Stories: Architecture and the Aftermath of the Lima Earthquake of 1746|website=Hispanic American Historical Review|doi=10.1215/00182168-83-1-53|access-date=3 July 2016 |last=Walker |first=Charles|volume= 83 |issue=1 |pp=53\u201382}}\n\n====Demographics====\n*{{in lang|es}} Instituto Nacional de Estad\u00edstica e Inform\u00e1tica, ''Perfil Sociodemogr\u00e1fico del Per\u00fa''. Lima: INEI, 2008.\n*United Nations Department of Economic and Social Affairs, ''Urban Agglomerations 2007''. New York (June 2008).\n{{refend}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons+cat}}\n{{Wikivoyage}}\n*[http://www.munlima.gob.pe/ Municipality of Lima] {{in lang|es}}\n*[http://www.gigapan.org/gigapans/60314/ 1.40 gigapixel image of Lima]\n*{{Wikivoyage-inline}}\n\n{{Lima landmarks}}\n{{Lima}}{{Navboxes\n|list=\n{{Navboxes\n|title=[[File:Gnome-globe.svg|25px]]{{nbsp}}Geographic locale\n|list=\n'''[[Geographic coordinate system|Lat. <small>and</small> Long.]