ungartistawards.org/nominees |archivedate=January 7, 2018 |df= }}</ref>\n|-\n| [[23rd Screen Actors Guild Awards|2017]]\n| [[Screen Actors Guild Award]]s\n| [[Screen Actors Guild Award for Outstanding Performance by an Ensemble in a Drama Series|Outstanding Performance by an Ensemble in a Drama Series]]  \n| {{won}}\n| <ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://www.ew.com/article/2016/12/14/2017-sag-awards-nominations|title=SAG Awards nominations 2017: See the full list|magazine=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|first=Joely|last=Nolfi|date=December 14, 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[9th Shorty Awards|2017]]\n| [[Shorty Awards]]\n| [[Shorty Awards|Best Actor]]\n| {{won}}\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=http://shortyawards.com/9th/gatenm123|title=9th Annual Shorty Awards|publisher=[[Shorty Awards]]|date=April 25, 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[24th Screen Actors Guild Awards|2018]]\n| [[Screen Actors Guild Award]]s\n| [[Screen Actors Guild Award for Outstanding Performance by an Ensemble in a Drama Series|Outstanding Performance by an Ensemble in a Drama Series]]\n| {{nom}}\n| <ref name=\"SAG Awards 2018\">{{cite news|last1=Gonzalez|first1=Sandra|title=The full list of the 2018 SAG Awards nominees|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2017/12/13/entertainment/sag-awards-nominations/index.html|accessdate=January 24, 2018|publisher=CNN|date=January 17, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[2018 MTV Movie & TV Awards|2018]]\n| [[MTV Movie & TV Awards]]\n| [[MTV Movie Award for Best On-Screen Duo|Best On-Screen Team]] <small>(with [[Finn Wolfhard]], [[Caleb McLaughlin]], [[Noah Schnapp]] and [[Sadie Sink]])</small>\n| {{nom}}\n| <ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/mtv-movie-tv-awards-2018-nominations-complete-list-1108100 |title=MTV Movie & TV Awards: 'Black Panther,' 'Stranger Things' Top Nominations |last=Nordyke |first=Kimberly |magazine=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=May 3, 2018 |accessdate=May 3, 2018 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180503235147/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/mtv-movie-tv-awards-2018-nominations-complete-list-1108100 |archivedate=May 3, 2018 |df=}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[2019 Teen Choice Awards|2019]]\n| [[Teen Choice Awards]]\n| [[Teen Choice Award for Choice Summer TV Star: Male|Choice Summer TV Actor]]\n| {{nom}}\n| <ref>{{cite magazine |last1=Swift |first1=Andy |title=Teen Choice Awards: Stranger Things Leads Final Wave of 2019 Nominations |url=https://tvline.com/2019/07/08/teen-choice-awards-nominees-2019-stranger-things-full-list-nominations/ |magazine=TVLine |accessdate=19 July 2019 |language=en |date= July 8, 019}}</ref>\n|}\n\ngreat performance on stranger things\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb name|7140802}}\n* {{IBDB name|491509}}\n\n{{ScreenActorsGuildAwards EnsembleTVDrama 2010\u20132019}}\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Matarazzo, Gaten}}\n[[Category:2002 births]]\n[[Category:21st-century American male actors]]\n[[Category:American people of Italian descent]]\n[[Category:American male stage actors]]\n[[Category:American male television actors]]\n[[Category:American male child actors]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Male actors from New Jersey]]\n[[Category:Male actors of Italian descent]]\n[[Category:People from Little Egg Harbor Township, New Jersey]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American actor and singer}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Gaten Matarazzo\n| image              = File:Gaten Matarazzo by Gage Skidmore.jpg\n| caption            = Matarazzo at the 2017 [[San Diego Comic-Con]]\n| birth_name         = Gaetano John Matarazzo III\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|2002|9|8}}\n| birth_place        = [[Connecticut, United States]]<ref>https://bestofnj.com/features/entertainment/things-didnt-know-gaten-matarazzo-stranger-things/</ref>\n| occupation         = Actor, singer\n| years_active       = 2011\u2013present\n}}\n\n'''Gaetano John''' \"'''Gaten'''\" '''Matarazzo III'''<ref>Matarzzo at {{cite AV media|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CEMeDw7dCb4|title=Stranger Things' Gaten Matarazzo Goes Undercover on Reddit, YouTube and Twitter|work=[[GQ (magazine)|GQ]]|date= July 1, 2019|accessdate= July 1, 2019|medium=www.youtube.com|time=00:46|quote=It's actually Gaetano John Matarazzo III.}}</ref> ({{IPAc-en|\u02c8|\u0261|e\u026a|t|\u0259n|_|\u02cc|m|\u00e6|t|\u0259|\u02c8|r|\u00e6|z|o\u028a}}; {{IPA-it|\u0261ae\u02c8ta\u02d0no mata\u02c8rattso|lang}}; born September 8, 2002)<ref>{{cite news|url= https://www.upi.com/Top_News/2019/09/08/UPI-Almanac-for-Sunday-Sept-8-2019/2621567647013/|title= UPI Almanac for Sunday, Sept. 8, 2019|agency= [[United Press International]] | date= September 8, 2019|accessdate=January 30, 2020 |archivedate= September 9, 2019|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20190909031013/https://www.upi.com/Top_News/2019/09/08/UPI-Almanac-for-Sunday-Sept-8-2019/2621567647013/|url-status=live|quote=\u2026actor Gaten Matarazzo in 2002 (age 17)}}</ref> is an American actor and singer. He began his career on the [[Broadway theatre|Broadway]] stage as Benjamin in ''[[Priscilla, Queen of the Desert (musical)|Priscilla, Queen of the Desert]]'' and as [[Gavroche]] in ''[[Les Mis\u00e9rables (musical)|Les Mis\u00e9rables]]''.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://www.playbill.com/personlistpage/person-list?production=00000150-aea8-d936-a7fd-eefc733d0003&type=op#oc|title=Les Mis\u00e9rables|magazine=[[Playbill]]|accessdate=August 18, 2016}}</ref> He stars as [[Dustin Henderson]] in the [[Netflix]] science-fiction-horror drama series ''[[Stranger Things]],'' and hosts the Netflix show ''[[Prank Encounters]]''. He is also the lead singer of the indie rock band Work In Progress.\n\n==Early life==\nMatarazzo was born in [[Connecticut]], to Gaetano and Heather Matarazzo, but raised in [[ Little Egg Harbor Township, New Jersey]], and he attended Pinelands Regional High School in [[Tuckerton, New Jersey]].<ref name=PromPhotos>{{cite news|url= https://www.nj.com/entertainment/2019/05/nj-stranger-things-star-gaten-matarazzo-shows-off-prom-photos.html|title=N.J. 'Stranger Things' star Gaten Matarazzo shows off prom photos|date=May 6, 2019|accessdate=January 30, 2020|first=Amy|last= Kuperinsky|publisher=[[New Jersey Advance Media]]|archivedate=January 30, 2020|archiveurl=http://archive.is/Ygf8J|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.j-14.com/posts/gaten-matarazzo-heather-matarazzo-150838/|title=Gaten Matarazzo and Heather Matarazzo: Are They Related?|date=2018-01-26|website=J-14|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-04}}</ref> He has two siblings, an older sister Sabrina and a younger brother Carmen.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.looper.com/156982/the-untold-truth-of-gaten-matarazzo/|title=The untold truth of Gaten Matarazzo|last=Santilli|first=Morgana|date=2019-06-28|website=Looper.com|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-04}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nMatarazzo is of [[Italians|Italian]] descent.<ref>[http://247.libero.it/lfocus/39105018/1/gaten-matarazzo-il-dustin-di-stranger-things-ha-famiglia-originaria-di-avellino/]</ref><ref>[http://www.ansa.it/sito/notizie/cultura/tv/2019/07/05/stranger-things-amicizia-batte-paura_ac7df6be-2e17-41ce-8ffc-9d7ee816074d.html]</ref>\n\nMatarazzo was born with [[cleidocranial dysostosis]], which he has spoken openly about, even documenting one of his surgeries, during which 14 [[supernumary teeth]] were removed, on [[Instagram]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://metro.co.uk/2020/02/02/stranger-things-star-gaten-matarazzo-gives-thumbs-successful-fourth-surgery-fourth-surgery-rare-bone-condition-complete-success-12168587/|title=Stranger Things star Gaten Matarazzo's surgery is a complete success|date=2020-02-02|website=Metro|language=en|access-date=2020-03-09}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Ro|first=Crystal|url=http://hellogiggles.com/dustin-stranger-things-loves-showing-off-fake-teeth-real-life-obviously-adorable|title=Dustin from \"Stranger Things\" loves showing off his fake teeth in real life, and obviously it's adorable|publisher=HelloGiggles.com|date=August 5, 2016}}</ref> After he was cast in ''[[Stranger Things]]'' as [[Dustin Henderson]], the character's background was modified to have the condition as well.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.inverse.com/article/20121-dustin-stranger-things-missing-teeth|title=Stranger Things: What Happened to Gaten Matarazzo's Teeth?|website=Inverse|language=en|access-date=2020-03-09}}</ref> He uses [[dentures]].<ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.ca/2016/09/28/gaten-matarazzo-disorder_n_12232838.html|title=Gaten Matarazzo Of 'Stranger Things' Talks About His Genetic Disorder|magazine=[[Huffington Post]]|date=September 28, 2016}}</ref>\n\nHe is a vegetarian.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://bestofnj.com/features/entertainment/things-didnt-know-gaten-matarazzo-stranger-things/|title=9 Things You Didn't Know About Gaten Matarazzo (Stranger Things)|date=2017-10-24|website=Best of NJ|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-09}}</ref>\n\n==Philanthropy==\nMatarazzo uses his platform to raise awareness of CCD and fundraise for CCD Smiles, an organization that helps cover costs of oral surgeries for people with CCD. Matarazzo has also started a line of T-shirts whose proceeds will go to CCD Smiles. On his social media sites, Matarazzo tells followers how to donate to CCD Smiles and promotes events he will participate in. In November 2017, his sister started a Facebook campaign to raise money for the organization.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://startsomegood.com/ccd-smiles|title=Donate to CCD Smiles!|publisher=StartSomeGood|accessdate=November 10, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ksl.com/?sid=46188187&nid=148&title=stranger-things-star-brings-smiles-to-utahns-with-rare-genetic-disorder|title='Stranger Things' star brings smiles to Utahns with rare genetic disorder|publisher=[[KSL-TV]]|location=Salt Lake City, Utah|accessdate=November 10, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+ Film and television \n! Year\n! Title\n! 